s\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  The USA defeated France 98-87 in the men's basketball final at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics on Saturday, extending their gold medal streak in the event to five in a row.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 392, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 405, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1998_FIFA_World_Cup\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3761680388605748e-28, \"text\": \"France 98\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1998_FIFA_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1998_FIFA_World_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coach Steve Kerr inserted Kevin Durant into the USA's starting lineup against host nation France, and he went 5-for-12 from the field to score 15 points while adding four assists, one steal and one block.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Kerr\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Kerr\"}, {\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.409385562306677e-28, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8934390289551574, \"rank\": 0.11911551253941813, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"Slim Reaper,\\\" who turns 36 next month, was also tasked with guarding Victor Wembanyama in the second half.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"score\": 0.9999841253320871, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Wembanyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 20-year-old French superstar is even thinner than Durant, but also much taller and younger than the two-time NBA Finals Most Valuable Player (MVP).\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9490985894106168, \"rank\": 0.03625547244163027, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 991, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\", \"score\": 0.9999996678416762, \"rank\": 3.234995983882595e-07, \"text\": \"NBA Finals\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals\"}, {\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\", \"score\": 0.9999999990536708, \"rank\": 8.378442609316403e-10, \"text\": \"Most Valuable Player (MVP)\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Most_valuable_player\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although it was not a decision Kerr wanted to make, he had no choice but to lean heavily on Durant, because Wembanyama proved practically unstoppable on the way to pouring in a game-high 26 points.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1123, \"end\": 1129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.409385562306677e-28, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant might be the only player on the USA's roster able to match the French center in agility while also being tall enough to deflect his shots.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1268, \"end\": 1271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9490985894106168, \"rank\": 0.03625547244163027, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LeBron James (#6) of the USA dunks in the men's basketball final at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France, August 10, 2024.\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1472, \"end\": 1477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999986252988, \"rank\": 1.3747189702999054e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8934390289551574, \"rank\": 0.11911551253941813, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  The USA started the game with a strategy aimed at speeding up the tempo and going for easy transition buckets on fastbreaks.\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1514, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France managed to slow down the Americans in the second half, however, while showing solid discipline and aggression on the defensive end.\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8934390289551574, \"rank\": 0.11911551253941813, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hosts also opted to put more muscles on Durant and Devin Booker on defense, in order to disrupt their shooting rhythm.\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1818, \"end\": 1824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.409385562306677e-28, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}, {\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7664036746877874e-38, \"text\": \"Devin Booker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As for the USA's prime playmaker LeBron James, Guerschon Yabusele and Evan Fournier worked hard to deny him the ball.\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1909, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1968, \"end\": 1981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Fournier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evan Fournier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Fournier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Fournier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as the Americans were prevented from running their offense through James, the team's scoring options were more limited.\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2091, \"end\": 2096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0220074977325272e-17, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Wembanyama put back a missed shot by Yabusele in the fourth quarter, France trailed by just three points, 82-79.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8934390289551574, \"rank\": 0.11911551253941813, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the rest of the game belonged to Stephen Curry.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1513704089409302e-45, \"text\": \"Stephen Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry attempted 14 shots overall and connected on 8-of-13 from three-point range.\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Four of those triples came in the fourth quarter and all were classic long-distance \\\"Curry Threes,\\\" rather than textbook outside shots.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Curry (R) of USA takes a shot in the men's basketball final at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France, August 10, 2024.\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1513704089409302e-45, \"text\": \"Stephen Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}, {\"begin\": 2556, \"end\": 2559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.918902023864849, \"rank\": 0.07486386015026013, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2634, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999986252988, \"rank\": 1.3747189702999054e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8934390289551574, \"rank\": 0.11911551253941813, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  \\\"Before every shot you take, you think it's going in,\\\" Curry said after the game.\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All I saw was the rim.\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2777, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not see who was in front of me.\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I knew it was kind of a late clock situation, but that one impressed myself.\\\"\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have seen that from Steph a few times, but it never gets old,\\\" Kerr said of Curry.\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2918, \"end\": 2923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"score\": 0.9999998422622536, \"rank\": 1.2868516832964092e-07, \"text\": \"Steph\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a global game with a lot of great players, but we still feel we have the greatest players.\\\"\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 3078, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"James, 39, once again contributed a stroing all-around performance, tallying 14 points, six rebounds, 10 assists, two steals and one block.\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3080, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0220074977325272e-17, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just living in the moment, super humble that I can still play this game and play it at a high level,\\\" James said.\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3329, \"end\": 3334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0220074977325272e-17, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It came with us winning gold and that's what's more important for me.\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's pretty cool.\\\"\", \"from\": 3412, \"to\": 3430, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3692, \"entities